348
00:20:58.534 --> 00:21:02.414
But proliferation was the strength of the neuroepithelial stem cells.

349
00:21:02.834 --> 00:21:06.794
So these guys that move very slowly or stay stationary, their

350
00:21:06.814 --> 00:21:07.734
job is to proliferate.

351
00:21:09.524 --> 00:21:11.894
And this is already then summarizing the entire talk.

352
00:21:11.994 --> 00:21:15.943
I hope I've shown you first insights into the different gene

353
00:21:15.974 --> 00:21:19.754
expression profiles across these different molecular subclasses of

354
00:21:19.814 --> 00:21:23.663
supratentorial ependymoma and the new clusters that were identified recently,

355
00:21:24.454 --> 00:21:28.244
which are starting to understand how they are spatially localized at

356
00:21:28.254 --> 00:21:31.794
primary tumor diagnosis as well as relapse over time.

357
00:21:31.874 --> 00:21:35.834
And again, the first few early days of defining what the phenotype in the

358
00:21:35.894 --> 00:21:36.594
brain might be,

359
00:21:37.894 --> 00:21:41.074
those glial ependymoma-like cells that stay stationary and extend

360
00:21:41.084 --> 00:21:45.074
their little extensions, we don't know what

361
00:21:45.094 --> 00:21:46.914
their job is yet, and looking into that as well.

362
00:21:47.644 --> 00:21:50.214
And that's all to say that this is, of course, only the first step.

363
00:21:50.954 --> 00:21:54.834
Now the next step is to look at what can we inhibit in terms of behavior

364
00:21:55.394 --> 00:21:59.034
and what are the programs that we need to block to hopefully finally make

365
00:21:59.334 --> 00:22:00.574
some headway for these patients.

