737
00:42:48.270 --> 00:42:51.210
citraconate is able to abrogate this metastatic phenotype.

738
00:42:52.790 --> 00:42:56.570
Now, citraconate is a tool compound, so translation is

739
00:42:56.590 --> 00:43:00.520
potentially difficult for this. So we then went back,

740
00:43:00.570 --> 00:43:02.400
took a step back, and said: What are the

741
00:43:03.210 --> 00:43:06.390
metabolic pathways that are leveraged to make itaconate?

742
00:43:06.870 --> 00:43:10.130
And from some metabolic tracing studies, we identified glutamine.

743
00:43:10.550 --> 00:43:13.310
Glutamine provides four of the carbons in itaconate.

744
00:43:13.330 --> 00:43:17.070
Itaconate is a five-carbon metabolite, so four of the carbons come from glutamine.

745
00:43:17.130 --> 00:43:21.040
So we thought, can we inhibit glutamine metabolism to now

746
00:43:21.090 --> 00:43:23.930
lower itaconate levels? And I'm showing you some of the data here.

747
00:43:24.650 --> 00:43:28.519
If we inhibit glutamine metabolism using this compound, GHU 083,

748
00:43:28.590 --> 00:43:32.570
which is a glutamine antagonist, you can see a similar drop in the fusion

749
00:43:32.610 --> 00:43:36.010
level. So what we're doing is, again, this RelA blot, and this is the higher

750
00:43:36.070 --> 00:43:36.950
molecular weight. You can

751
00:43:37.970 --> 00:43:41.750
mimic this by using this glutamine antagonist, and the fusion levels drop.

752
00:43:43.190 --> 00:43:44.890
The survival curve is also very similar.

753
00:43:45.470 --> 00:43:49.010
If you take animals that are vehicle-treated versus glutamine antagonist

754
00:43:49.390 --> 00:43:53.290
treatment, you can see there's a survival benefit in these animals as well in

755
00:43:53.330 --> 00:43:54.930
the IuE immune intact models.

756
00:43:56.670 --> 00:43:58.250
So from these data,

757
00:43:59.210 --> 00:44:02.960
we concluded that inhibiting ACOD1 or glutamine is therapeutic in

758
00:44:03.010 --> 00:44:04.190
these animal models.

759
00:44:05.720 --> 00:44:08.610
So I think I'm going to summarize what I've told you so far.

760
00:44:09.350 --> 00:44:12.950
So first, we identified that the ZFT Rel Ependymomas

761
00:44:13.070 --> 00:44:17.050
made this immunomodulatory metabolite that has been described extensively in

762
00:44:17.110 --> 00:44:19.370
macrophages but not in tumors, called itaconate.

763
00:44:20.870 --> 00:44:24.130
Itaconate inhibition actually lowered the fusion

764
00:44:24.210 --> 00:44:27.990
levels in vitro and in vivo, and this was both at the

765
00:44:28.010 --> 00:44:31.310
genetic level and at the pharmacological level, providing maybe a

766
00:44:31.350 --> 00:44:35.310
really interesting mechanism to pursue to directly target the fusion

767
00:44:35.350 --> 00:44:36.070
protein itself.

768
00:44:37.090 --> 00:44:41.070
And then the mechanism that we stumbled on is that itaconate behaves like an

769
00:44:41.130 --> 00:44:45.090
oncometabolite. Because of its similar structure to alpha KG, it inhibits

770
00:44:45.150 --> 00:44:49.110
histone demethylases, specifically what we looked at is KDM5,

771
00:44:49.470 --> 00:44:52.829
and increases this activation mark to drive fusion expression.

772
00:44:53.610 --> 00:44:57.330
And if we could target this pathway either with a tool compound, dimethyl

773
00:44:57.390 --> 00:45:01.090
itaconate, or an upstream glutamine antagonist, this

774
00:45:01.130 --> 00:45:04.710
created a survival benefit in these IuE immune intact models.

775
00:45:06.030 --> 00:45:09.050
So we proposed this model where ZFT Rel fusions

776
00:45:09.630 --> 00:45:13.230
upregulate ACOD1, and this ACOD1, in turn,

777
00:45:13.590 --> 00:45:17.530
is required to drive this fusion by itaconate production.

778
00:45:17.950 --> 00:45:21.450
And itaconate can be supplied by glutamine to produce

779
00:45:21.490 --> 00:45:25.230
itaconate. And there's a positive feedback loop where itaconate

780
00:45:25.250 --> 00:45:28.990
behaves as an oncometabolite, increases this activating

781
00:45:29.050 --> 00:45:32.750
mark at the ZFTA regulatory element, and there's a

782
00:45:32.870 --> 00:45:36.750
positive feedback loop. And you can interrupt this positive feedback loop at

783
00:45:36.810 --> 00:45:40.470
two nodes that I showed you, either at the ACOD1 node by genetic

784
00:45:40.510 --> 00:45:43.920
knockdown or using these two different inhibitors that we used,

785
00:45:44.430 --> 00:45:47.990
or with an upstream GHU 083 that has been used in clinical trials in

786
00:45:48.030 --> 00:45:52.010
adults. And you can interrupt this pathway by decreasing

787
00:45:52.050 --> 00:45:54.950
the fusion levels itself. So I

788
00:45:54.990 --> 00:45:56.150
think

789
00:45:57.370 --> 00:46:01.210
as Mariella alluded to, there's no treatments for these children except radiation,

790
00:46:01.310 --> 00:46:05.190
so there's potential promise to think of ideas of leveraging this

791
00:46:05.230 --> 00:46:09.010
pathway. And then finally, I wanted to give a shout-out to the Cat Car

